  .container.content-section
    .row
      .col-md-4
        .highlighted-content-header Community Involvement
        .subhead-content-box
          .subhead giving back

      .col-md-8
        .body-copy Part of Technekes' culture is rolling up our sleeves and getting involved and making a difference. There are many ways we do this and many groups we work with - both related and unrelated to business.

.container
  .row.content-section
    .col-md-4.col-xs-12
      = image_tag "charities/RMHCLogo.png", class: "center-block charity-logo"
    .col-md-8
      .row
        .col-sm-12.col-xs-10.col-xs-offset-1.col-sm-offset-0
          .highlighted-content-box
            .subhead Red shoe shootout
          .charity-body-copy Our own Jack Ross is a nationally ranked shooter, so helping him found and sponsor the Ronald McDonald House of Charlotte Red Shoe Shootout has been a natural fit for us. Since the first Shootout in 2011, Technekes has also provided organizers, teams, volunteers, and of course, one heckuva sharpshooter.
          %a.uppercase-link{href: "http://www.rmhofcharlotte.org/", target: "_blank"} Visit site

  .row.content-section
    .col-md-4.col-xs-12
      = image_tag "charities/allinlogo.png", class: "center-block charity-logo"
    .col-md-8
      .row
        .col-sm-12.col-xs-10.col-xs-offset-1.col-sm-offset-0
          .highlighted-content-box
            .subhead all-in to fight cancer
          .charity-body-copy  When a mutual friend was diagnosed with cancer, Steve and Scott banded some friends together to found All-In To Fight Cancer, which hosts Texas Hold'em fundraisers around the country, with all proceeds going back to the local cancer community of healthcare providers, families, and survivors.
